-- China Life H1 net profit up 13.6 pct, beats forecasts
-- By Lawrence White
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 05:45AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 27 (Reuters) - China Life Insurance Co Ltd <2628.HK> <601628.SS>, the world's biggest insurer by market capitalization, said on Wednesday first-half net profit grew 13.6 percent, above analysts' forecasts.

The company said in a stock exchange filing in Shanghai it had earned 18.4 billion yuan ($3 billion) in the first six months of the year, up from 16.2 billion yuan a year ago.